events.description: The Utah Museum of Fine Arts, the state's primary cultural resource for global visual arts, showcases a world-class permanent collection of art objects from the classical to contemporary periods and presents some fifteen rotating exhibitions annually. Highlights include European and American masterworks, art of Utah and the American West, and emerging contemporary art from around the world. Programs, most of them free, include artist talks, films, and family art-making activities. Museum store and cafe
events.location: Marcia and John Price Museum Building  410 Campus Center Drive  Salt Lake City, UT 84112

events.description: Red Butte Garden is Utah’s Botanical Garden and part of the University of Utah. It is the largest botanical garden in the Intermountain West that tests, displays and interprets regional horticulture. Explore over 100 acres including display gardens and natural area hiking trails. “Four Seasons, A Million Reasons” to visit for floral shows, outdoor concerts, camps and classes.
events.location: 300 Wakara Way  Salt Lake City, UT 84108

events.description:
Thanksgiving Point is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization located in Lehi, and is one of the best places to visit in Utah. It’s known for hosting several popular events including the Tulip Festival, an annual Half Marathon, the Scottish Festival, and Cornbelly's Corn Maze. 
Not only does Thanksgiving Point host events in Utah County, but it’s also the perfect destination for a variety of fun things to do and see including the 55-acre Thanksgiving Point Gardens and the Museum of Ancient Life, which is one of the world's largest dinosaur museums. There's also shopping at the Emporium and dining at the Tower Deli and Harvest Restaurant. 
If you like more physical activities, visit the 18-hole golf course or check out Brick Canvas at Thanksgiving Point, which features Bikram Yoga, Lyceum fitness center, a spa and salon. As you plan your visit, be sure to mark us as a must-do in your event calendar for Utah. 
Connect Pass Attraction - includes one admission to Gardens and Museum of Ancient Life.
